Currently there isn't a whole lot of logging in JIM. When we create the initial JDBC connection nothing and the connection times out, the importer just spins, in the detailed logs all you get is "creating new issues'. In the application logs of Jira it will show the last JDBC connection then nothing. 

 

It would be nice if we handled timeouts more eloquently, did some sort of pre-install issue count then sent back  a status or something. 

 

