h3. Problem Definition
JIRA Datacenter can share lucene index between nodes on request. In some cases this lucene index can be corrupted at specific node, in that case that node still can reply and propagate that index to other nodes (nodes copy it from shared folder), thus affecting whole cluster. 

h3. Suggested Solution
Potential "_donor_" node should detect that index is corrupted (and possibly not healthy) and should not reply to request. 

h3. Note
There is similar check already in *backupIndex()*, see JRASERVER-64927
{noformat}
public String backupIndex(String requestingNode, final IndexSnapshotContribution contribution) {
...
final Long latestOperation = ofBizNodeIndexOperationStore.getLatestOperation(nodeId);
 if (latestOperation == null) {
    LOG.warn("Index backup failed - latest index operation not found. Requesting node: {}", requestingNode);
   return null;
 }
{noformat}
so node refuses to share index if it does't have index operations.

h3. Workaround 
None

h3. Problem Definition:
Referring to our Public REST API Documentation below, it mentions the use of "fields" as a shorthand for "set":
- https://docs.atlassian.com/software/jira/docs/api/REST/7.6.1/#api/2/issue-editIssue

But, the usage of both in one REST Call does not seem to be working where I'm getting the error whenever I tried to do the same as in the example:
{code}
{
    "errorMessages": [
        "Can not deserialize instance of java.util.ArrayList out of START_OBJECT token\n at [Source: org.apache.catalina.connector.CoyoteInputStream@6bdb7269; line: 3, column: 43] (through reference chain: com.atlassian.jira.rest.v2.issue.IssueUpdateBean[\"update\"])"
    ]
}
{code}

h3. Suggested Solution:
Update the documentation by differentiate the example when using the "fields" and "updates" to prevent any confusion.

h3. Notes:
The documentation is mentioning about the use of {{editmeta}} GET REST to find the details of the Editable fields for the issue. Here it mentions about "Fields" and "Update" parameter as well where so far, I could not find any field under the "Update" parameter from it.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-33995].
  {panel}

Basically re-create the expand feature from Confluence for JIRA comments. This would enable users to simply throw any content the comment author doesn't want to be displayed by default in a nice expand macro to be displayed once clicked. This would allow comments to be more structured, and allow larger content, such as error logs, etc. to be submitted via comments.

